# ECP Specification Rules

- `spec.yaml` is the canonical example ECP Context manifest.
- TypeScript types in `src/types/ecp.ts` are the single source of truth for the schema. If you add a new field to `spec.yaml`, add the corresponding type — the JSON Schema is auto-generated from the types.
- After editing types or `spec.yaml`, run `npm run check` to regenerate the schema and validate.
- After editing any `.md` file, run `npm run lint:md` to check markdown lint.
- Never hand-edit `dist/ecp-context.schema.json` — it is a build output generated by `npm run generate:schema`.
